  <h3 class="welcome-title ">The Project Development</h3><br/>
  <h3 class="welcome-subtitle">
    PDFind is a web app that utilizes Google's
    <a class="a-h3" href="https://developers.google.com/identity/protocols/oauth2">Oauth 2.0 </a>  
    and 
    <a class="a-h3" href="https://developers.google.com/gmail/api">Gmail API </a> 
    to access a user's inbox and provide a
    </br> filterable list of pdf attachments. 
    </br> The back-end was developed using 
    <a class="a-h3" href="https://nodejs.org/"> Nodejs </a>
    and 
    <a class="a-h3" href="https://expressjs.com/"> Expressjs </a>
    , check out GitHub to see the
    </br> source code and list of all dependencies used. 
    </br>The front-edd was developed using HTML, CSS, and Javascript, 
    </br>with some help from 
    <a class="a-h3" href="https://getbootstrap.com/"> Bootstraps </a>
    and 
    <a class="a-h3" href="https://ejs.co/"> EJS. </a>
  </h3> </br>
